This paper proposes a method for maximum likelihood estimation of energy-based models using a neural generator network. The paper focuses on generating sharp images and anomaly detection, which are common topics in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of nonparametric mutual information estimators suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the use of a gradient penalty suggests a focus on stochastic differential equations (cs.SD). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.LG and cs.CV, followed by cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.SD.
